Patch Set 1:

Hmm.  I'm questioning the need for POLICY-3256, when deleteByConceptKey() can already be used to delete particular templates by name & version - seems safer than deleting by name only.

Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1:
> 
> Hmm.  I'm questioning the need for POLICY-3256, when deleteByConceptKey() can already be used to delete particular templates by name & version - seems safer than deleting by name only.

Yes name and version will only delete one record at a time which is safer.

Patch Set 1:

> Patch Set 1:
> 
> Hmm.  I'm questioning the need for POLICY-3256, when deleteByConceptKey() can already be used to delete particular templates by name & version - seems safer than deleting by name only.

Yes, we need to think about this more. The deelteByConceptkey() is on Dao level but is not exposed above that. Also what worries me is referential integrity, of a concept is referred to by another concept then should we allow it to be deleted? Also though, maybe we need a "super user" ability so that a "super user" can update and delete concepts in the unlikely (;-D) event of things getting mucked up.

Also I'd like to have a more generic way of doing CRUD for TOSCA concepts, we have a good few TOSCA concepts int here now that are all almost identical (type and corresponding instance), if we have a bespoke API that covers all the concepts it's going to get very unwieldy

Patch Set 1:

> Also though, maybe we need a "super user" ability so that a "super user" can update and delete concepts in the unlikely (;-D) event of things getting mucked up.

Is it time to bump the priority on user roles?

Abandoned

We need to rethink how we are working with service templates.

Patch Set 1:

(3 comments)

It seems to me that all validations checks are covered by the 4 following rules:

* restControllerShouldOnlyDependOnRestController
* apiServiceShouldOnlyDependOnControllerAndServices
* spiServiceShouldOnlyDependOnControllerAndServices
* repositoryIsOnlyAccessedByServicesAndRepository

To simplify the tests, why not keeping only these ones if they are also covering all the others ones ?

Also, if ever needed, you can give a look to Lang API at https://www.archunit.org/userguide/html/000_Index.html#_the_lang_api to see how to combine predicates and conditions with something like:

  .that().resideInAPackage("..service..")
  .or().resideInAPackage("..persistence..")
  .should().accessClassesThat().resideInAPackage("..controller..")
  .orShould().accessClassesThat().resideInAPackage("..ui..")

Patch Set 1:

Two reasons led to this change:
- During a review with sylvain we found "common.mariadbService" was defined wrongly in (_mariadb.tpl) which was correct in this change (https://gerrit.onap.org/r/c/oom/+/121074).

- There was a problem during installing a component with local mariadb instance, that we need to have some kind of logic to decide which db to use (the shared one or local installation) [in the case of CDS we used ternary function].

What I am trying to do in this change is to make use of the both defined templates (common.mariadbService) and (common.mariadbPort) to reflect the actual mariadb service name and port in the cases of localCluster is enabled
